race.comment: SWEET LOVE (6) is a fast beginner who has shown good improvement at her last two starts, the latest scoring at Geelong over 400m. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to her name from seven starts. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. IS HE HAPPY (5) rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when second (22.64) at Murray Bridge over 395m. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Expected to be in the finish again. PINAROO FLYER (1) settled down midfield and held his position to the line when finishing 4th (22.24) at Shepparton. Has placed several times at this track. Bold showing expected. THIS BLACK DUCK (2) has an unbeaten record from this draw, scoring two times.
